  "name": {
    "en": "Chamomile",
    "zh-Hant": "洋甘菊",
    "zh-Hans": "洋甘菊"
  },
  "scientificName": "Matricaria chamomilla",
  "family": "Asteraceae",
  "genus": "Matricaria",
  "description": {
    "en": "Chamomile is an annual plant of the daisy family, native to Europe and western Asia. The flowers are used medicinally for their calming and anti-inflammatory properties.",
    "zh-Hant": "洋甘菊是菊科一年生植物，原生於歐洲和西亞。其花朵因具有鎮靜和抗炎特性而被用於藥用。",
    "zh-Hans": "洋甘菊是菊科一年生植物，原生於欧洲和西亚。其花朵因具有镇静和抗炎特性而被用于药用。"
  },
  "commonName": {
    "en": "German Chamomile",
    "zh-Hant": "德國洋甘菊",
    "zh-Hans": "德国洋甘菊"
  },
  "botanicalDescription": {
    "en": "Annual herb growing 15-60 cm tall. Leaves are bipinnate or tripinnate, finely divided. Flowers are white ray florets surrounding yellow disc florets, 1-2 cm in diameter.",
    "zh-Hant": "一年生草本植物，高15-60厘米。葉為二回或三回羽狀，細裂。花為白色舌狀花圍繞黃色管狀花，直徑1-2厘米。",
    "zh-Hans": "一年生草本植物，高15-60厘米。叶为二回或三回羽状，细裂。花为白色舌状花围绕黄色管状花，直径1-2厘米。"
  },
